http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Pampa-Sangamom-on-January-6/article13978274.ece

The Travancore Devaswom Board will organise a spiritual and cultural meet, Pampa Sangamom, at Pampa on the foothills of Sabarimala on January 6, board president Prayar Gopalakrishnan has said.Chief Minister Oommen Chandy will inaugurate the meet at the Ramamurthi Mandapam at Pampa Manalpuram at 4 p.m. on Wednesday. He said the meet had been organised as a prelude to declaring Sabarimala an international pilgrimage centre. The meet would also help make Sabarimala popular across the globe, he said.From other StatesO. Paneerselvam, Tamil Nadu Finance Minister, will deliver the keynote address and P.J. Kurien, Deputy Chairman of Rajya Sabha, will be the guest of honour at the meet. Devaswom Minister V.S. Sivakumar will preside over the inaugural function.Manikyala Rao, Andhra Pradesh Devaswom Minister; E. Indrakaran Reddy, Telangana Devaswom Minister; A. Manjunath, Minister for Animal Husbandry in Karnataka; R. Kamaraj, Food and Devaswom Minister of Tamil Nadu; Ramesh Chennithala, Home Minister; Adoor Prakash, Revenue Minister; Thiruvanchoor Radhakrishnan, Forest Minister; K.P. Mohanan, Agriculture Minister; V.K. Ebrahimkunju, Works Minister; Ajay Tharayil and P.K. Kumaran, TDB members, will also address the function.K. Babu, Sabarimala Special Commissioner; Anto Antony, MP; K. Sivadasan Nair, Raju Abraham, MLAs; and others will also attend the function.